Synchronization:
Unconditional: thread.sleep - java method or class look it up
Conditional:

Wait in Selenium:
Implicit:
Explicit: WebDriver (also called just Explicit Wait)
		  Fluent Wait
		  
PageLoadTimeOut - will wait until the page is fully loaded. Applicable only for page and used for commands .get() and .navigate();

Implicit Wait - will tell the driver to wait until specified time before its throws NoSuchElementException.
Works with .findElement and .findElements

It implicitly wait for every element in your program. If element is found within 2 seconds -> rest of the time will be ignored
if not found program will wait specified amount of time and ONLY then will throw NoSuchElementException.


